verses.verse: A Psalm <WH4210> of David. <WH1732> The earth <WH776> is the LORD's, <WH3068> and the fullness <WH4393> thereof; the world, <WH8398> and they that dwell <WH3427> therein.
For he has founded <WH3245> it on the seas, <WH3220> and established <WH3559> it on the floods. <WH5104>
Who <WH4310> shall ascend <WH5927> into the hill <WH2022> of the LORD? <WH3068> or who <WH4310> shall stand <WH6965> in his holy <WH6944> place? <WH4725>

He that has clean <WH5355> hands, <WH3709> and a pure <WH1249> heart; <WH3824> who <WH834> has not lifted <WH5375> up his soul <WH5315> to vanity, <WH7723> nor <WH3808> sworn <WH7650> deceitfully. <WH4820>

Who <WH4310> is this <WH2088> King <WH4428> of glory? <WH3519> The LORD <WH3068> of hosts, <WH6635> he is the King <WH4428> of glory. <WH3519> Selah. <WH5542>
